# Code

## pig-latin.rs

```rust,editable,ignore
//! A Pig Latin converter that iterates over each string and changes it to pig latin.
//! Each iteration should run on a separate thread.

use std::thread;

fn main() {
    let mut v = vec![String::from("hello"), String::from("apple"), 
                      String::from("strong"), String::from("world")];

    for word in v.iter_mut() {
        thread::spawn(move || {
            // Change the word to pig latin here
        });
    }
}
```

## Cargo.toml

```toml
{{#include ../../examples/concurrency-pig-latin/Cargo.toml}}
```

## Running Our Code

We will run our code with the following command. We should get `['ellohay', 'appleay', 'ongstray', 'orldway']`.

```bash
cargo run
```
